healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Medical Supplies and Enteral Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for medical supplies and enteral services with a retail purchase or cumulative rental cost over $500.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Second Opinion
healthcare_rules.rule_content: The member's PCP must refer the member to an in-network care provider for a second opinion. Direct requests to UnitedHealthcare Community network care provider are not allowed.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Commercial Oral Nutritional Supplements
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for commercial oral nutritional supplements. We cover the assessment provided by the member unless the member is also receiving nutrition through PCP as part of the EPSDT screening specified in enteral or parenteral feedings.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization and Notification Requirements
healthcare_rules.rule_content: For prior authorization, visit the Prior Authorization and Notification. A current list of CPT codes that require prior authorization can also be found there.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Oncology Prior Authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: For oncology services, prior authorization is required. Contact 1-888-397-8129 for the current list of CPT codes that require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Request Prior Authorization for Covered Prescriptions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Request prior authorization to see which prescriptions require prior authorization or are not covered or preferred.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Additional Exams
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Additional exams require prior authorization. This should be obtained by the PCP/PCO from Nationwide Vision.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: DME Prior Authorization Exemptions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Durable medical equipment (DME) does not require prior authorization unless the individual is of age or on the Prior Authorization List.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Baby's Birth Report
healthcare_rules.rule_content: The ALTCS EPD (LTC) requires prior authorization for reporting a baby's birth.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Community Plan Members
healthcare_rules.rule_content: UnitedHealthcare requires prior authorization for certain services for Community Plan members.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Laboratory Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for laboratory services ordered by a PCP or dentist, except as noted on prior authorization requests consistent with coverage limitations.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Advanced Outpatient Procedures
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for Advanced Outpatient Procedures, including plastic surgery imaging procedures. Use the Provider Portal for a prior authorization crosswalk and/or clinical guidelines.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Out-of-Network Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all out-of-network services. Documentation must be submitted to support referrals.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Check Prior Authorization Requirements
healthcare_rules.rule_content: For a list of services that require prior authorization, go to UHCprovider.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Verify AHCCCS Codes for Prior Authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Check AHCCCS codes for services requiring prior authorization by submitting claims. This is necessary for valid and approved codes.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Exhaust remedies before appealing under IDEA
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Local educational agencies must follow the payer's appeal process and exhaust all remedies before appealing under 34 CFR Part 300; or the covered service can be considered.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Electronic Claims Submission Frequency
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Electronic claims submissions must be made Monday-Friday. Include the original claim number in loop 2300.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Report fall diagnosis codes for member death or serious injury
healthcare_rules.rule_content: UnitedHealthcare Community Plan requires reporting member death or serious injury associated with a fall diagnosis code on claim submissions. This requirement began on April 1, 2018.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Proper Format for FQHC/RHC Claim Submissions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: For FQHC/RHC claim submissions, the 9-digit AHCCS County, Type, District, School CTDS identifier must be provided without a space or separator between 0B and the CTDS number. This applies to CMS 1500 Claim Form Box 19, ADA Claim Form Field 35, and 837 Professional (Electronic Claim) Loop 2300 NTE number and name. A visit's reimbursement will be applied to the HCPCS Examples code T1015.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Submit Claims for Community & State Facet Claims
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Mail initial medical claims and medical record attachments to UnitedHealthcare Community Plan P for Community & State Facet claims.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Corrected Claim Submission Requirements and Reconsiderations
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Requirements and claim reconsiderations can be found in Chapter 14 of this manual.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Claims Submission Deadline Calculation
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Deadlines for claims submission are calculated from the claim end date of service, inpatient claim date of discharge, or the effective date of eligibility posting, whichever is later.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Corrected Claims Submission Requirements
healthcare_rules.rule_content: When submitting a corrected paper CMS 1500 claim, include the claim resubmission code in Box 22. Use the appropriate resubmission code for errors such as invalid frequency code, missing, or replacement of the original claim number.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Out-of-Network Referrals
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all out-of-network referrals. Documentation to support the referrals must be submitted.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Required Immunization and Tuberculosis Records for Lifetime
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Immunization and tuberculosis records are required for lifetime. This means these records must be maintained throughout a patient's lifetime.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Supervision by Licensed Professional for Assistants
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Documentation must indicate supervision by a licensed professional for assistants providing services. This applies to prescribing controlled substances or medications that interact with them.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Requirements for CPT Codes
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for certain CPT codes. Visit the Prior Authorization and Notification for a current list of codes that require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Oncology Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Authorization for oncology services requires prior authorization. Contact 1-888-397-8129 for the current list of CPT codes that require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Services Requiring Prior Authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Services requiring prior authorization must have a valid member ID number, referring and servicing care providers, and current applicable CPT, ICD-10 Diagnosis, and HCPCS codes. The member must meet with the PCP before receiving treatment if follow-up care is recommended.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Follow new guidelines for physical health billing
healthcare_rules.rule_content: For CMS 1500 claim forms, use new guidelines for physical health billing or state T1015. Behavioral health may deny claims if these guidelines are not followed.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: EVV Hard Edit Claim Denial Rule
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Electronic visit verification hard edit results in claim denial for in-scope claims with a service date of January 1, 2023. Additional requirements may apply to UB claims.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Coding Requirements for UHC Arizona Members
healthcare_rules.rule_content: UHC Arizona requires the use of UB-04 forms for hospital inpatient services and compliance with state and federal coding requirements for outpatient services, dialysis services, and skilled nursing services starting April 1, 2018, for services provided in homes and long-term care facilities.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Check coverage and price before filling prescriptions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Request prior authorization to see which prescriptions require prior authorization or are not covered or preferred. Check coverage and price, including lower-cost alternatives.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Requirements for Certain CPT Codes
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for CPT codes that serve a medical purpose and are ordered or prescribed by a care provider. Evidence-based clinical guidelines must be followed.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Some Admissions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for SNF admissions, except for those noted on the prior authorization list. Planned or elective admissions for acute care laboratory services ordered by a PCP or other care provider do not require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Substance Use Education
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for substance use education. This is to educate patients about their substance use and motivate them to change their behavior.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Out-of-Network Referrals
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all out-of-network referrals to prevent the deterioration of a condition.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Opioid Storage and Disposal Prescription Limits
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Opioids require prior authorization. Storage and disposal of opioids must follow prescription limits.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Dispute Overpayment Findings within Timely Filing Limits
healthcare_rules.rule_content: If you disagree with overpayment findings, submit a dispute within the required time frame, which may vary by state.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Services Not Covered by UnitedHealthcare District Dual Choice Plan
healthcare_rules.rule_content: UnitedHealthcare District Dual Choice Plan does not cover services that are not medically necessary, provided outside the plan scope, or covered by Medicaid. This includes intermediate care facility services, waiver services for individuals with intellectual or developmental disabilities, and behavioral health and substance use care.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Required Immunization and TB Records for Lifetime
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Immunization and TB records are required for lifetime. This means these records must be maintained throughout a patient's lifetime.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Contact UHC for CPT code list and more information
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Call 1-866-889-8054 for a CPT code list and more information. Review authorization basic requirements and guidelines.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Request Prior Authorization for Radiology Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: To request prior authorization for radiology services, review the authorization basic requirements and guidelines. Contact 1-866-889-8054 for the list and more information.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Coding: Prior Authorization for Non-Medical CPT Codes
healthcare_rules.rule_content: CPT codes not useful without illness, disability, or injury require prior authorization. These codes must be ordered or prescribed by a care provider according to evidence-based clinical guidelines.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Substance Use Education
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Current CPT codes require prior authorization for substance use education intervention. This is to alert providers to possible consequences and motivate them to change their behavior.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Submit Resolving Claim Issues Drug Billed Coding
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Submit the HCPCS/CPT code and units of service for the Resolving claim issues drug billed, along with the actual metric decimal quantity administered.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Cardiology Procedures
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for certain cardiology procedures, including restorative and diagnostic catheterizations, unless performed in specific places of service. Standard ADA coding guidelines apply to all claims.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Requirements for Certain CPT Codes
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for CPT codes that serve a medical purpose and are ordered or prescribed by a care provider. This includes codes related to a prior disability or injury. A crosswalk table is also available for reference.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Some Acute Care Admissions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for SNF admissions, except for those noted on UHC's prior authorization list. Planned or elective admissions for acute care laboratory services ordered by a PCP or other provider do not require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Opioid Storage and Disposal Limits
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Opioids require prior authorization. Storage and disposal of opioids are subject to prescription limits.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Services Not Covered by UnitedHealthcare District Dual Choice Plan
healthcare_rules.rule_content: UnitedHealthcare District Dual Choice Plan does not cover services that are not medically necessary, provided by non-doctors, or covered by Medicaid. This includes intermediate care facility services, waiver services, and behavioral health and substance use care.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Contact UHC for CPT Code List and More Information
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Call 1-866-889-8054 for the CPT code list and more information on prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Review or request prior authorization for radiology services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: To review or request prior authorization for radiology services, see the authorization basic requirements and guidelines. Contact 1-866-889-8054 for the list and more information.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Coding: Prior Authorization for Non-Medical CPT Codes
healthcare_rules.rule_content: CPT codes not useful without illness, disability, or injury require prior authorization. These codes must be ordered or prescribed by a care provider based on evidence-based clinical guidelines.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Substance Use Education
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for substance use education. This is to alert providers to possible consequences and motivate them to change their behavior.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Cardiology Procedures
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for certain cardiology procedures, including restorative and diagnostic catheterizations. However, cardiology procedures do not require prior authorization if performed in standard places of service. Standard ADA coding guidelines apply to all claims.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Routine TTY 711 Vision Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all routine TTY 711 vision services through March Vision Care.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Get Prior Authorization for General Practice 1
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for general practice 1. This can be obtained from the specified practice areas.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Check coverage and price for prescriptions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Request prior authorization to see which prescriptions require prior authorization or are not covered or preferred. Check coverage and price, including lower-cost alternatives.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Lab Services Prior Authorization Exemption
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Medically necessary lab services ordered by a PCP, other care providers, or Home hospice dentist do not require prior authorization, except as noted on the UnitedHealthcare Community Plan covers benefits authorization list.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Requirements for Certain Medications
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for certain medications, including those that may be oral, injectable, or inhaled. A prior authorization crosswalk table and/or evidence-based clinical guidelines can be found at UHCprovider.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Out-of-Network Referrals
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all out-of-network referrals, including protective supervision for mentally impaired individuals. Accompaniment to medical appointments is also subject to prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Opioids Requiring Prior Authorization with Prescription Limits
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Opioids requiring prior authorization have prescription limits. Check the UHC Drug Lists and Pharmacy page for more information.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Confidential Information Disclosure for Dispute Procedures
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Confidential information is only shared with business associates and affiliates who need it for credentialing or care management. They must follow the dispute procedures in your Agreement.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Complete Appeal Process First
healthcare_rules.rule_content: The appeal process must be completed before any other steps. No further details are provided.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Submit Claims Within 90 Days
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Submit claims within 90 days of the claim submission date. Timely filing limits can vary based on state.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Referral Required for Prior Authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization for services requires a referral from the member's primary care physician (PCP). This includes services such as home care and pregnancy termination services.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Support Medical Necessity with Documentation
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Submit documentation to support medical necessity of requested procedure. Be aware services may be outside authorized scope. Determine if member has other insurance to bill first.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: List of CPT Codes for Prior Authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Review or request prior authorization for radiology services. Contact 1-866-889-8054 for the basic requirements, guidelines, CPT code list, and more information.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Certain Medications
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for medications that require close monitoring, ongoing clinical support and management, and complete patient education. These medications may be oral, injectable, or inhaled. Check the UHC provider website for a current list of CPT codes that require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Include CLIA Number Units of Service in Claims
healthcare_rules.rule_content: National Clinical Laboratory Claims must include the HCPCS/CPT code and units of service for the CLIA number.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Residential SUD Notifications Stays
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all residential SUD Notifications stays.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Periodontics services do not require prior authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Periodontics services are a self-referral service and do not require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Exhaust Health Plan's Appeal Process Before State Fair Hearing
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Before requesting a State Fair Hearing, providers must complete the health plan's appeal process.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Claim Submission Date or PRA Required
healthcare_rules.rule_content: You will see the adjustment on the EOB. Claim submission date or provider remittance advice (PRA) is required.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Support Medical Necessity with Documentation
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Submit documentation to support medical necessity of the requested procedure. Be aware that services may be outside the scope of UnitedHealthcare Community Plan's medical and drug policies. Determine if the member has other insurance that should be billed first.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Request Prior Authorization for Cardiology Care
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Review or request prior authorization for cardiology care by calling 1-877-610-9785 for requirements, guidelines, and CPT code list. More information is available through the CareModel (caremanagement/ IN_CareManagement@uhc).

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Use Prior Authorization and Notification Tool for Admission Notification
healthcare_rules.rule_content: To notify UHC of a medical prior authorization, use the Prior Authorization and requests/advanced and Notification Tool online. This includes EDI transactions 278 and 278N for admission notification.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: List only 1 demographic update per submission
healthcare_rules.rule_content: When submitting demographic updates, list only one update per submission.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Contact Information
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Call Customer Service at 1-866-675-1607 for services requiring prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Urgent or Emergent Hospital Care
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for urgent or emergent nonemergent/non-urgent hospital medical care. This applies to out-of-network care.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Urgent or Emergent Care
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for urgent or emergent medical care when receiving out-of-network services.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Prenatal Cessation Counseling
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for cessation counseling within the prenatal period.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Oncology Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: For Optum oncology services, prior authorization is required. Contact 1-888-397-8129 for the current list of CPT codes that require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Exceptions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is not required, except as noted on our prior authorization list.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Advanced Outpatient Imaging Procedures
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for advanced outpatient imaging procedures that require brief interventions. Screening results indicating at-risk behavior trigger this requirement.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization for Out-of-Network Referrals
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for all out-of-network referrals. The proposed policy and procedure will include both existing and proposed language.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Some Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for some services. This includes prior services.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Submit Claims Using a Clearinghouse
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Claims should be submitted using a clearinghouse, as per dispute procedures.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Follow Appeal Process on FFS Claims and Encounter Submissions
healthcare_rules.rule_content: When an enrollee appeals a clinical or coverage determination, follow the appeal process on FFS claims and encounter submissions.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Timely Filing Limits for Recoupment
healthcare_rules.rule_content: We will provide written notification within 1 year of the claim paid date if we seek to recoup overpayment following an audit or review. Timely filing limits can vary based on state review.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Claim Submission Procedures and Timely Filing Guidelines
healthcare_rules.rule_content: UnitedHealthcare Community Plan publishes a care provider manual online, which includes claim submission procedures, timely filing guidelines, billing and prior authorization policies, and a dispute and resolution process.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Referral Required for Prior Authorization Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization services require a referral from the enrollee's primary care physician (PCP).

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Notify Hospital in Writing of Documentation Needs
healthcare_rules.rule_content: The attending physician and hospital are notified in writing when documentation is needed to support inpatient denials.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Lifetime Immunization and TB Records Required
healthcare_rules.rule_content: A history of physical examination, including immunization and TB records, is required for lifetime.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Optum Oncology Services
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Authorization for Optum oncology services requires prior authorization. Contact Optum at 1-888-397-8129 for the current list of CPT codes that require prior authorization.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: CPT Code List and Prior Authorization
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Review or request prior authorization for radiology services. A CPT code list is required for more information.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Prior Authorization Required for Elective Hip Arthroscopy
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Prior authorization is required for planned elective hip arthroscopy procedures with specific CPT codes.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Post-maternity care services require time documentation
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Post-maternity care services must include the amount of time spent with the patient in documentation. These services are time-based.

healthcare_rules.rule_title: Report NDC and units for outpatient clinical settings
healthcare_rules.rule_content: Submit the National Drug Code (NDC) on all claims with procedure codes for care provider-administered drugs in outpatient clinical settings. Report the most extensive procedures and units of service for the drug billed, including actual metric decimal quantity administered.
